name: Compute
description: >
  Conversation workflow step that evaluates Blue Expression Objects (BEX)
  and returns a result.

  Compute reads the current processing context and computes data. It does not
  mutate the document directly. If the result contains a changeset, that
  changeset is still only data; a separate Conversation/Update Document step
  must apply it.

type: Conversation/Sequential Workflow Step

expr:
  description: >
    Optional BEX expression. If present and no `do` body is used, the step
    result is the evaluated expression.

do:
  type: List
  description: >
    Ordered list of BEX statements. Items are intentionally not strongly typed
    in this repository version.

definition:
  description: >
    Optional reference to reusable compute logic. In a Conversation workflow,
    this is commonly a contract key in the current scope pointing to a
    Conversation/Compute Definition.

entry:
  type: Text
  description: >
    Entry function name to execute when `definition` or local `functions` are
    used.

constants:
  type: Dictionary
  description: >
    Named constants available to BEX through `$const`. Keys are constant names;
    values are arbitrary Blue values.

functions:
  type: Dictionary
  description: >
    Named reusable BEX functions. Keys are function names; values are function
    definitions. Function objects are intentionally not strongly typed in this
    repository version.

emitEvents:
  type: Boolean
  value: true
  description: >
    If true, and the computed result contains an `events` list, the Conversation
    workflow processor emits those events.

returnResult:
  type: Boolean
  value: true
  description: >
    If true, the computed result is stored under the workflow step name and can
    be referenced by later steps.

gasLimit:
  type: Integer
  description: >
    Optional maximum gas allowed for this Compute step. If omitted, the host
    processor chooses the applicable default.